properties.areaDesc: San Diego County Mountains; Riverside County Mountains
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 10 at 3:13AM PST until February 10 at 4:00PM PST by NWS San Diego CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow occurring. Plan on difficult travel conditions,
including during the morning commute. Tree branches could fall
as well. Additional snow accumulations of 2 to 4 inches expected
for the Riverside County Mountains. Additional accumulations of
3 to 7 inches expected in the San Diego County Mountains, with
localized amounts of 6 to 12 inches at the highest elevations
near Mount Laguna.

* WHERE...The Mountains of Riverside and San Diego Counties above
5000 feet. Heaviest at the higher elevations of the San Diego
County Mountains.

* WHEN...Until 4 PM today.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Be prepared for reduced visibilities at
times.
properties.instruction:
A Winter Weather Advisory for snow means periods of snow will
cause primarily travel difficulties. Be prepared for snow covered
roads and limited visibilities, and use caution while driving.

For road condition information in California...enter
8 0 0 4 2 7 7 6 2 3 if inside california or
9 1 6 4 5 5 7 6 2 3 if outside California.
